.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-STATUS" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.16" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-status \- Show tracked scheduler state and log locations
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose status [OPTIONS]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Read tracked submission metadata and query the scheduler to show current batch state, runtime paths, log locations, and placement details.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Compose specification file to read. Default: compose.yaml.
.TP
\fB--job\-id\fR \fIJOB_ID\fR
Tracked Slurm job id to inspect instead of the latest recorded submission.
.TP
\fB--format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format. Possible values: text, json.
.TP
\fB--squeue\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the squeue executable. Default: squeue.
.TP
\fB--sacct\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the sacct executable. Default: sacct.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose status \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose status \-f compose.yaml \-\-format json
.fi
